RECTOR (Visual Repair)**\nMinor visual OCR confusions were corrected:\n- 'እንደሚጐትት' was corrected to 'እንደሚጎትት' (replacing 'ጐ' with 'ጎ').\n- 'አለመጐተቱን' was corrected to 'አለመጎተቱን' (replacing 'ጐ' with 'ጎ').\nNo attached punctuation was found.\n\n**Scholarly Guesses (Corrections based on linguistic context):**\n- 'በሚደያርገው' was corrected to 'በሚደረገው'. The original form 'ሚደያርገው' is not a standard Amharic verb conjugation; 'ሚደረገው' (by what is done/conducted) is a morphologically sound and contextually appropriate passive relative clause form of 'ማድረግ' (to do/make).\n- 'በተነረገለት' was corrected to 'በተደረገለት'. Similar to the above, 'ተነረገለት' is not a standard form. 'ተደረገለት' (for what was done for him/it) is a common and correct passive relative clause form of 'ማድረግ'.\n- 'ካልተዘየደለት' was corrected to 'ካልተጨመረለት'. The verb 'መዘየድ' is extremely rare or non-existent in modern Amharic with this meaning. 'መጨመር' (to add, to increase) provides a more plausible and common interpretation for the context, forming 'ካልተጨመረለት' (if it was not added for him/it).\n- 'ብሔረሰቦትና' was corrected to 'ብሔረሰቦች'. 'ብሔረሰቦት' is an incorrect plural form; 'ብሔረሰቦች' is the correct plural of 'ብሔረሰብ' (ethnic group/nationality).\n\n**PROTOCOL 4, 5, 6: THE LEMMATIZER, THE TRANSLATOR, THE GRAMMARIAN**\nFor each valid and cleaned word, its base dictionary entry (root), comprehensive English synonyms, and Part of Speech (POS) were identified and assigned. Proper nouns were lemmatized to their base form (e.g., 'ኤሴንዶን' to 'ኤሴንዶ').\n\n**PROTOCOL 8: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY**\nThis summary reflects the application of all protocols, detailing splits, discards, corrections, and scholarly guesses made to ensure the highest linguistic accuracy and adherence to the specified output format.","input_words":["የዝሆኖችን","ተአንተም","እንዳልተሳተፉና","የሚያብራሩበትን","ከኮሎምቢያዋ","አስቆማለሁ","እንደሚጐትት","አለመጐተቱን","የኤሴንዶን","ቦምበርስና","የኮሊንግተን","ማግፒስ","እንዳቀጣጠለው","አንቦገቦገው","ትሮሃማ","በሚደያርገው","ዳሰሳችንም","በአፍሪካዊነታቸው","ፋርማሲስቷን","ለመድፈኛው","ለሞልቴዶ","የሚያሸበርቁበት","በተነረገለት","ካልተዘየደለት","ብሔረሰቦ